																		Author Post
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/thedeadlymoose" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(732274); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=732274&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183034" alt="thedeadlymoose" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=732274)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/thedeadlymoose" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(732274); return false;" >thedeadlymoose</a></span> <span class="odate time_1536039992 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">04 Sep 2018 05:46</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3954782">
									

<p>This was a strange SCP to write, rewrite, and repost. It is an SCP I disagree with. I do not believe it is, or should be, canon. I don't agree with its premise. I disagree strongly with its moral universe. Even though I'm responsible for its thematic backbone. It is not part of anything I've written outside the Doomsday Contest.</p>
<p>This may not make sense to anyone, but my parts of this were heavily inspired by <a href="/scp-3999">SCP-3999</a>, the collective works of <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;">djkaktus</a></span> starting with <a href="/scp-2935">&quot;O Death&quot;</a> onward, the works and perspectives of many long-gone site members, and a hell of a lot of deleted SCPs.</p>
<p>This piece would not exist without <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dexanote" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(481882); return false;">Dexanote</a></span>, <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drewbear" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(301632); return false;">Drewbear</a></span>, and <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/weizhong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1777811); return false;">weizhong</a></span>. weizhong wrote the entire myths section, and edited the entire piece extensively. Drewbear wrote the original history (and brought in all the Bowe stuff), and made many fixes. Dexanote shaped the original idea, before (and while) I went off the deep end with it. All three read and edited the piece before posting.</p>
<p>Thank you to <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/modern-erasmus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3129691); return false;">Modern_Erasmus</a></span>, <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/petrograd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(455145); return false;">Petrograd</a></span>, <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/toa-vine" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2023146); return false;">Toa_Vine</a></span>, <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ihp" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1267048); return false;">Ihp</a></span>, and <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tl333s" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1304786); return false;">TL333s</a></span> for leaving <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-6254940/deletions-52:proper-storys-supposed-to-start-at-the-beginnin#post-3855617">valuable feedback</a> on the original article. This version was massively, <span style="text-decoration: underline;">massively</span> rewritten, and I hope the piece works better.</p>
<p>Special thanks to <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dreverettmann" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(323946); return false;">DrEverettMann</a></span> for edits and contributing a text suggestion (a poem excerpt).</p>
<p>This is part of the <a href="/project-palisade">Project Palisade</a> storyline, which is, at least for now, complete. So hopefully this doesn't go down in flames!</p>

							</div>

								
