				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/nathaniel-prime" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1609974); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1609974&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183034" alt="Nathaniel Prime" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1609974)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/nathaniel-prime" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1609974); return false;" >Nathaniel Prime</a></span> <span class="odate time_1538710133 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">05 Oct 2018 03:28</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4014234">
									

<p>This entry is magnificent, and I'm confused why you would put down such a good entry, especially one written in collaboration with others. The only thing wrong with it is the extra cruft attached to it, like the testing logs. This entry can stand on it's own without twenty links to existing and new articles, so let it. Less is more.</p>
<p>But when I say that's the only thing wrong with that, I really mean it. This piece itself is amazing. Wonderful idea of a ruthless Foundation, making copies of itself to delay (or will it?!) some sort of reality-eating entity which cannot currently be seen, much less understood or fought. The writing was also excellent. It also explains how everything on this site can be as it is. I would have liked more direct explanation of what the worm was, though I'm pretty sure I've figured it out correctly and that in any case it is mostly a matter of personal preference.</p>
<p>Easily earns a place among the other excellent 001's!</p>

							</div>

								
					
