				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/weizhong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1777811); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1777811&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183034" alt="weizhong" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1777811)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/weizhong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1777811); return false;" >weizhong</a></span> <span class="odate time_1536040383 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">04 Sep 2018 05:53</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3954797">
									

<p>This has been quite the trip, and as Moose said, it was an odd piece of fiction to write. I view this as almost like an alternative fiction &quot;What if?&quot; version of the SCP canon that was a lot of fun to speculate about, even if none of us ultimately agreed with this version of history.</p>
<p>It took a lot of work to translate our original version into what you see today, and I have to thank Moose for taking the brunt of the effort with regards to reworking the entire piece, as well as Dex and Drew for reviewing the work we put together. Ultimately, I think we've come up with something that's much stronger overall, and hopefully tells the story of Palisade that we intended from the very start.</p>

							</div>

								
					
