				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/the-great-hippo" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3938622); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3938622&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183034" alt="The Great Hippo" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3938622)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/the-great-hippo" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3938622); return false;" >The Great Hippo</a></span> <span class="odate time_1536067388 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">04 Sep 2018 13:23</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3955479">
									

<p>I really enjoyed this; the prose itself is extremely polished, the idea is both horrible and has a cruel internal logic, and the execution has a number of clever turns. It also neatly explains a lot of incongruities with the setting without relying on some sort of hackneyed third-act &quot;THE FOUNDATION ISN'T REAL!&quot; twist. It felt a <em>little</em> bloated to me at certain points, but that's likely just coming down to personal taste.</p>
<p>There's a lot of thematic and mechanical elements here that are similar to a tale series I've been messing with off and on for about a month, now. Presuming it's alright, I might want to use some of this stuff (or even ask you a couple of questions about it at some point in the future!).</p>

							</div>

								
